        org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClassExpression getRestriction(OWLReferencesInterface ontology)
        Computes the specific restriction with the specified value.
        Parameters:
        ontology - the representation that will host the restriction.
        Returns:
        the restriction that will be used to compute the axiom by getAxiom(OWLReferencesInterface).

      • addRestriction

        default org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyChange addRestriction(OWLManipulator ontoManipulator)
        Returns the changes to be done in order to add the specified restriction to an ontology. It is based on (getAxiom(OWLReferencesInterface)).
        Parameters:
        ontoManipulator - the manipulator to the representation that will host the restriction.

      • removeRestriction

        default org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyChange removeRestriction(OWLManipulator ontoManipulator)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the changes to be done in the ontology to remove the restriction.

      • getDataType

        default org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLDatatype getDataType(java.lang.Class c)
        It converts a java class in the related OWL data factory. Supported types are: Double, Float, String, Boolean, Long and Integer. It returns null if the input class is not supported.
        Parameters:
        c - the java class to be converted in a OWL data type.
        Returns:
        the OWL data type related to the input class, null if the type is not supported.
